---

Reassurance, as defined by [Cambridge Dictionary]():

> words of advice and comfort intended to make someone feel less worried

---

Why do people have the need to be reassured?

Reassurance in the workplace

* As a colleague
* As a manager

Reassurance in relationships

* 

When is too much reassurance?

* When no action is applied to the root of the cause
* Reassurance without action is temporary
    * Action from the one who needs it
    * Action from the one who provides it

Reassurance requires empathy

To reassure is a wonderful act, benefiting both parties, but for long-standing issues it can be a negative